        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "And Nadab and Abihu died {b} before the LORD, when they offered strange fire before the LORD, in the wilderness of Sinai, and they had no children: and Eleazar and Ithamar ministered in the priest's office in the {c} sight of Aaron their father.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "And Nadab and Abihu died ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{b}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " before the LORD, when they offered strange fire before the LORD, in the wilderness of Sinai, and they had no children: and Eleazar and Ithamar ministered in the priest's office in the ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{c}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " sight of Aaron their father.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(b) Or, before the altar.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(c) While their father lived.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The incident here referred to is related in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 10:1-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The meaning of ‘strange fire’ is uncertain. Either the incense which they burnt was not made in accordance with the divine prescription (given in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 30:34-38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). or the fire was not taken from the proper place—the altar of burnt-offering. ‘Strange’ means ‘not in accordance with the regular ritual’; see n. on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 1:51",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "they had no children",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The point of this lies in the fact that after the exile all the priestly families called themselves ‘sons of Aaron,’ and traced their descent through Eleazar or Ithamar (see p. xvi).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
